messageBody:
If you've downloaded the ePub version of Call of Cthulhu somewhat recently, you might've gotten an error complaining about attributes without values if you've gotten to chapter 2. This update fixes that error.

Available at https://github.com/adiabatic/qs-literature/ like always.

Change list:

- s/perfession/profession/
- s/subjuct/subject/g
- s/perfessional/professional/
- "supposed" ends in [d] (as an adjective; this isn't universal)
- s/[siNgul@`]/siNgjUl@`]/g
- s/[totlI]/[tot@lI]/g
- s/[QbdZ@kt]/[QbdZEkt]/
- oh right, XML (can't do <a b></a>, have to do <a b='b'></a>)
